cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing. The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The introduction of a new layer for local reordering of input sequences could also suggest a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of Sleep-WAke Networks (SWAN) for sequence modeling could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as SWAN has been previously used for image segmentation.
